  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function set_uniform_1f(uniform_location: Number(gint), value: Number(gfloat)): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_pipeline_set_uniform_1f()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Sets a new value for the uniform at <code>uniform_location</code>. If this
pipeline has a user program attached and is later used as a source
for drawing, the given value will be assigned to the uniform which
can be accessed from the shader's source. The value for
<code>uniform_location</code> should be retrieved from the string name of the
uniform by calling <link xref="Cogl.Pipeline.get_uniform_location"/>.</p>  <p>This function should be used to set uniforms that are of type
float. It can also be used to set a single member of a float array
uniform.</p>
  <p>Since 2.0</p>
